(EAST CRAZIES EXAMPLE SOILS SCOPE OF WORK) Tj T*
() Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Date: 2026-05-07) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Audience: WLG demonstration package) Tj T*
(Purpose: show that the system can produce resource-area scopes of work for a new NEPA project from a) Tj T*
(structured project intake) Tj T*
(Example project: East Crazy Inspiration Divide land exchange) Tj T*
(Forest: Custer Gallatin National Forest) Tj T*
(District: Bozeman Ranger District) Tj T*
(Resource area: Soils) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(This example assumes a new project is in early planning, before late-stage NEPA materials or resource) Tj T*
(analysis packages exist. The SOW is generated from the proposed action, project location, preliminary) Tj T*
(action elements, parcel/trail/access features, likely resource triggers, and standard public source) Tj T*
(requirements.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(This is the capability WLG should see: the system can translate the controlling source stack into a) Tj T*
(tight specialist-report SOW. For this soils example, the stack includes NEPA, current USDA NEPA) Tj T*
(procedures, NFMA/project-consistency requirements, Forest Service handbook and manual direction,) Tj T*
(Region 1 soil management direction, the applicable Forest Plan, soil-quality monitoring methods,) Tj T*
(National BMPs, and official soil-survey data. The SOW turns those sources into fieldwork, analysis,) Tj T*
(deliverables, and acceptance criteria that should produce a defensible soils specialist report) Tj T*
(without pretending the planning package has already made a NEPA or legal sufficiency determination.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(For the East Crazies example, the soils scope is driven by:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- proposed new or rerouted trail segments;) Tj T*
(- trailhead improvements;) Tj T*
(- stream crossings, wetland/riparian approaches, wet soils, hydric soils, erosion, and sediment) Tj T*
(  delivery;) Tj T*
(- parcel restrictions, access/easements, grazing-related improvements, and acquired-parcel soil) Tj T*
(  management needs.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The consultant product is a Soils Specialist Report or, if approved by the Forest Service soils) Tj T*
(reviewer, a short issue-screening memo. Either product must support later EA drafting, Forest Plan) Tj T*
(consistency documentation, mitigation commitments, and implementation planning.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(This is a planning and contracting support SOW. It is not a final agency decision, legal sufficiency) Tj T*
(review, or NEPA compliance determination.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
